Traitors' Shameless Intention Brought to Light 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- Documents related to the south Korea-Japan "talks" in the period from 1951 to 1965 was opened to the public in south Korea, touching off great resentment of the Korean nation. These documents recording the whole process of the "talks" have brought to light the fact that the south Korean rulers sold off the dignity and interests of the nation to Japan for a few pennies of money.
 The traitorous group of south Korea did not mention the issue of liquidating the past crimes committed by the Japanese imperialists including the assessment of their past history, illegality of the Korea-Japan "annexation treaty" and the issue of individual claims of the victims during their occupation of Korea. And they failed even to set the nominal amount claimed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun Sunday carries a signed commentary. It goes on:
 At the political bargaining with Japan the south Korean dictatorial regime sold off the dignity and interests of the nation for a penny of money and covered up the past crimes of Japan. This is an unpardonable crime against the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the documents, Japan raised a brigandish demand just like a thief crying "stop thief". The Japanese reactionaries threatened to appeal to the International Court of Justice, asserting that Tok Islet belongs to Japan. Finally at the talks, they insisted on blowing up the controversial islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is now working hard to gloss over the crimes related to sexual slavery committed by the imperial Japanese army while talking about the final solution to the issue of postwar reparation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States manipulated behind the scene the whole course of the "talks" and the fabrication of "agreements" with a view to forming the triangular military alliance by establishing "normal relations" between south Korea and Japan and using the alliance to materialize its Korea and Asia strategy for aggression.
 Japan and the U.S. are the sworn enemy of the Koreans as they have done harm to the interests of the Korean nation through despicable and base swindles and conspiracy.

Signature Campaign for Pullback of U.S. Troops in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The Pilgrimage Group for Peace against War and Pullback of the U.S. Troops in south Korea is reportedly conducting a signature campaign for withdrawal of the U.S. troops in different parts of south Korea.
 The group arrived in Kwangju on September 3 and explained the justness of the U.S. troops' pullback among citizens. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In Inchon on September 11 the group called for waging an all- people anti-U.S. struggle and distributed copies of literature demanding the withdrawal of the U.S. troops among citizens. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The group conducted the signature campaign in Mokpho, South Jolla Province and in North Chungchong Province before expanding the campaign to Chonan and other areas of South Chungchong Province.

Russian Vice-Foreign Minister on Relations with DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Moscow, September 9 (KCNA) -- Alekseyev, Russian vice-foreign minister, addressing a reception given at the DPRK embassy in Moscow on September 8 on the occasion of the 57th anniversary of the DPRK, said that the long-standing traditional relations of friendship between the two countries are  now developing on good terms as in the past.
 The former Soviet Union was the first in the world to recognize the sovereignty of the DPRK and the two countries have since cooperated with each other in the international arena, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Foreign Ministry and many other state organs of Russia have striven to develop the friendly relations with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The two countries have initiated constructive proposals and put them into practice to develop cooperation in different fields including politics, economy and culture and made joint efforts to ensure peace in Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russia has deep interests in the development of inter-Korean relations and positively striven to make the six-party talks a favorable leverage to promote reconciliation and cooperation between the north and the south of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the reception laid a floral basket and bouquets before a full-length portrait of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il.
 The reception was followed by an art performance given by a Russian art troupe and staff members of the DPRK embassy.

Egyptian Presidential Envoy Visits DPRK Embassy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cairo, September 9 (KCNA) -- We sincerely wish the Korean people greater success in their struggle for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation and national reunification under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.
 The special envoy of Egyptian President Mohamed Hosni Mubarak said this when visiting the DPRK embassy in Cairo on September 8 on the occasion of the 57th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that it was an honor for him to convey the warm congratulations of Mohamed Hosni Mubarak to Kim Jong Il and the government and people of the DPRK on the occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The leadership, government and people of Egypt have valued and attached great importance to the historical relations with the DPRK, a fraternal and friendly country, he stressed.

UFL Joint Military Exercises Denounced in Britain
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The British Association for the Study of Songun Policy and the British Association for Friendship with Korea released a joint statement on September 3 denouncing the U.S. for staging the "Ulji Focus Lens-05" joint military exercises in south Korea.
 The war maneuvers were aimed at invading the DPRK, the statement said, noting that as they were launched on the eve of the day the six-party talks were expected to be resumed, thus preventing any progress from being made in the efforts to seek a negotiated solution to the nuclear issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is that the war exercises were timed to coincide with the appointment of the presidential envoy for the north Korean human rights issue, the statement said, terming this an outrageous interference in the DPRK's internal affairs.
 The statement fully supported the DPRK's stand to have the six-party talks adjourned till mid-September. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It strongly urged the U.S. imperialists to immediately stop all their war drills for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Extending invariable firm solidarity to the DPRK standing on the forefront for the world revolution and independence in order to defend the people-centered socialist system, the statement praised the DPRK as a fortress of Songun towering imposingly in Asia.

Anti-U.S. Do-or-Die Resistance Declared in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The All-People Measure Committee for Checking the Expansion of the U.S. Military Base in Phyongthaek of south Korea reportedly held a candlelight meeting in Phaengsong-up in Phyongthaek City, Kyonggi Province, on Sept. 3 at which it declared do-or-die resistance to check the expansion of the U.S. military base.
 At the meeting speakers recalled that a year has passed since the anti-U.S. candlelight demonstration staged in Phyongthaek in protest against the expansion of the U.S. military base on Sept. 1 last year, calling upon all the people to fight it out with a strong will for an anti-U.S. struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that their candlelight meeting would be a prelude to a struggle for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A declaration read out at the meeting stressed that any threat or appeasement of the U.S. will not work on them and they will launch do-or-die resistance for defending their land.

Art Performances Mark DPRK's Birthday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Art performances were given in different parts of the country on the occasion of the 57th anniversary of the DPRK.
 The revolutionary drama "Under the Banner of Victory" was staged at the State Theatrical Theatre.
 The drama helps the audience recall with deep emotion the immortal exploits President Kim Il Sung performed by winning a shining victory in the confrontation with the U.S. in the 1950s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The audience hardened their resolution to work hard for the prosperity of the DPRK and the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche under the uplifted banner of Songun, rallied close around leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the State Comic Troupe gave a performance "Let's Go Cheerfully" at the Pyongyang Grand Theatre, and an acrobatic performance was given at the Pyongyang Circus Theatre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performances provided the audience with opportunities to feel once again the pride and happiness of living and working as citizens of socialist Korea in which the people have become true masters of state power and renew their pledge to make patriotic devotion to the prosperity of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, music and dance performances were given in various capitals of provinces including North Phyongan, South Hamgyong, Jagang and Kangwon provinces and a performance was given by art groups of officials and employees of the provincial-level institutions in South Phyongan Province.

Evening Galas of Youths and Students Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Evening galas of youths and students were held in different parts of the country on September 9 on the occasion of the 57th anniversary of the DPRK.
 Youths and students in Pyongyang had evening galas in different parts of the city including the squares in front of the Tower of the Juche Idea and the Monument to Party Founding. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They started when "Song of the Proclamation of the People's Republic" resounded forth. 
 The participants in the evening galas danced to the tune of songs "Pyongyang Is Best", "Our General Is Best", "Pride of Youth", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Youths and students in different provincial capitals, cities and county seats held similar events on the same day evincing their determination to add shine to the DPRK.

Intensified Struggle for Withdrawal of U.S. Troops from S. Korea Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The deputy chief of the Japan Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front released a statement on September 8  60 years since the U.S. troops' occupation of south Korea, according to Internet site "Kuguk Jonson".
 The statement called for focusing all efforts on the struggle for the withdrawal of the U.S. troops to make this year a year of the U.S. troops' pullback from south Korea and a year in which the Koreans will be able to live in the idea of "By our nation itself" free from U.S. domination and interference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 60 year-long presence of the U.S. troops in south Korea clearly proved that the U.S. imperialists are the root cause of all sorts of misfortune and pain the Korean people have suffered and their desire for independence, democracy and reunification can never be achieved as long as the U.S. troops stay in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation living in the era of June 15 independent reunification is not what it used to be in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle for independence against the U.S. has become an irresistible trend of the times and it is the present reality that all Koreans are out in the courageous struggle for the withdrawal of the U.S. troops to make this year, which marks the 60th anniversary of the U.S. troops' occupation of south Korea, a year of the withdrawal of the U.S. troops. There is no place on this land for the U.S. troops to stay.

Banquet Given to Mark DPRK Birthday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government arranged a banquet at the People's Palace of Culture here on Friday evening in celebration of the 57th birthday of the DPRK.
 Addressing the banquet, Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, said that the DPRK is the benevolent motherland, which provided the Korean people with the position and dignity of being genuine masters of the country and society for the first time in the nation's history of 5,000 years, and a socialist state of Juche which brings to reality the popular masses' independent ideal and provides them happiness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung built a prosperous socialist power in this land, which had suffered an eclipse on the world map as a colony of the imperialists for many years, the speaker noted, stressing that his feats for nation-building will remain forever with the annals of the cause of Juche which is making a long drive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is now demonstrating its independent dignity and potentials more fully than ever before under the ever-victorious Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il, the speaker noted, and said: As long as there is his Songun leadership, the DPRK will dynamically advance along the road of Juche revolution despite of any challenges of history and remain prosperous and powerful forever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We, he further said, will decisively smash the moves of separatists at home and abroad under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and surely achieve the historic cause of national reunification by the concerted efforts of the entire nation.
 Denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula is the behests of    Kim Il Sung, and it is the consistent stand of the DPRK government to settle the nuclear issue through dialogues, he said, adding: We will do our utmost to solve the nuclear issue in a peaceful way and realize the denuclearization of the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government will steadily strengthen solidarity with the progressive people of the world in the idea of independence, peace and friendship and strive to build an independent and peaceful new world, the speaker stated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the banquet were senior party, state and army officials, chairpersons of friendly parties and members of the Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present on invitation were diplomatic envoys of different countries, representatives of international organizations here and foreign guests.

Arirang Performed in Celebration of DPRK's Birthday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- A grand gymnastic and artistic performance Arirang was given at the May Day Stadium Friday evening in celebration of the 57th anniversary of the DPRK.
 Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Jong Ha Chol, Kim Jung Rin, Choe Yong Rim, Jang Song U and Chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party Kim Yong Dae took the platform. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tribune of honor was also occupied by Ko Tok U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan who is leading the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Foreign guests staying in the DPRK watched the performance. 
 The performers impressively portrayed the history of the Korean nation which has traversed the road of victory and glory under the seasoned and veteran leadership of the peerlessly great men through music, dance, gymnastics, acrobatics, rhythmic background scenes, peculiar stage settings, electronic displays and laser lightings deep in national emotion and high in ideological and artistic value.

Wreaths Laid before Cemeteries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt Taesong and the Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery on Friday on the occasion of the 57th anniversary of the DPRK.
 Seen in the wreath-laying stand was a wreath sent by Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Kim Yong Nam, Pak Pong Ju, Choe Thae Bok, Kim Il Chol and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths were laid in the name of the WPK Central Committee, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet amidst the playing of the wreath-laying music. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then wreaths were placed in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, working people's organizations, ministries, national institutions, KPA units, scientific, educational, public health and press organs, and party and power organs, factories, farms and schools in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid a silent tribute to the memory of revolutionary and patriotic martyrs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths were also laid before the statues of martyrs, revolutionary martyrs' cemeteries, the monument to fallen fighters of the People's Army and graves of martyrs in different parts of the country on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, floral baskets were  placed before the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War on Friday on the occasion of the anniversary.

End to U.S. Policy of Occupation of S. Korea Demanded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The policy of occupation of south Korea pursued by the United States for the last 60 years is a product of its strategy to dominate the Korean nation, says Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed article.
 The U.S. imperialist aggression troops landed in Inchon Port under the pretext of "disarming" the defeated Japanese imperialists 60 years back when the Koreans were aspiring after the building of an independent and sovereign state, rejoiced at the fact that the heroic anti-Japanese war waged by them culminated in putting an end to the 40 odd year-long Japanese imperialists' colonial rule over Korea. 
 The U.S. forces' talk about "disarming the Japanese troops" was no more than an excuse, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Japan declared an unconditional surrender on August 15, 1945. In actuality, the U.S. forces did not disarm the Japanese imperialists but kept the Japanese colonial repressive machines including police organs and rallied pro-Japanese traitors in a desperate bid to establish their ruling system in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bolstered its armed forces in south Korea and made attempts to invade the north from the very day of its forces' landing in a bid to dominate the whole of Korea.
 It ignited the Korean war in the 1950s to realize this plan. The U.S. ambition for invading the north remained unchanged even after imposing unspeakable disasters upon the Korean nation and sustaining a bitter defeat in the war.
 The desire for reunification is growing stronger on the Korean Peninsula. But the U.S. is getting frantic in its moves to invade the north while ceaselessly beefing up the combat power of the U.S. forces present in south Korea so as to realize those moves.
 The reality proves that the Korean people cannot save its destiny unless they put an end to the U.S. policy of occupation of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koreans can live in peace and achieve reunification and prosperity only when the U.S. forces are driven out of south Korea.

GNP's Anti-Reunification Racket under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland in a statement Saturday bitterly denounced in the name of the whole nation the Grand National Party of south Korea for whipping up distrust and confrontation between the north and the south and laying a big obstacle to the efforts to implement the June 15 joint declaration and develop the north-south relations, going against the aspiration of the fellow countrymen for reconciliation, unity and reunification.
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP was so dishonest and unreasonable as to find fault with the sincerity and favor the north showed for the delegation of the south Korean authorities by broad-mindedly and lucidly clarifying a series of issues arising in the inter-Korean relations during its visit to Pyongyang on the occasion of the fifth anniversary of the June 15 joint declaration. As to the north delegation's visit to the "Memorial" while staying in Seoul during the August 15 grand national festival, the GNP hurled vituperation at the north, claiming that it was a "psychological warfare peculiar to the north" and little short of digging a "pitfall" and south Koreans should not be taken in by it. Worse still, it egged ultra-right conservatives on to seriously vilify the north, asserting that the festival was manipulated by someone behind the scene.
 Meanwhile, the GNP is weaving a plot to build up a new pro-U.S. and anti-north conservative group made up of such living dead as Ri Hoe Chang already forsaken by history and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such moves of the GNP are stirring up the resentment of the whole nation as they were prompted by an attempt to dampen the tendency towards alliance with the north and reunification rapidly growing strong in south Korea, block the process of warming up the inter-Korean relations, stem the trend of the situation at any cost and take a position favorable for it in the local election next year and the 2007 "presidential election", the spokesman said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP should be thrown overboard as it is an anti-reunification traitorous party only adding to its crimes, obsessed by its inveterate consciousness of confrontation.
